<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Jubal:
[B]Looking back on it I wish I had put all my starting points into STA. I didn't though and I have a high elf cleric with a base 130 WIS, and I can't seem to drop enough WIS items to bring myself down to 200. All the WIS gear I have now has other stats that I'd be loath to lose.

First, the uber stuff that I assume I will be wearing for a very long time:

Lodizal Shell Shield (10 wis)
Girdle of Grotesque (10 wis)

The next level of items are things that have good stats for mana, hp, sta etc.:

Heirophant's Cloak (4 wis)
Coldain skin gloves (6 wis)
Ethereal mist BP (15 wis)
Ethereal mist legs (9 wis)
Obolus death shroud (3 wis)
Vambraces of Forbidden Rites (3 wis)

Finally I have the things that give WIS but I really dont have anything better to replace them with:

Dawnfire (7 wis)
Supple Scale armband (5 wis)
Enshrouded Veil (2 wis)

I also have a crown of hatred with 6 wis that I am not wearing at the moment, but I'd like to because I love the right-click instacast targetable UV effect.

All other pieces of gear I've already dumped WIS items for mana, hp, resists, and stamina. I have all the jewelcrafted resist items that I swap in when I need resists but don't think they are advantageous for normal ac/hp/mana play.

Anyone have any suggestions on what to look for in order to dump some of this WIS and get more ac, hp, sta and mana? I'll be getting my epic in the next few weeks most likely so that will further increase the number of WIS points I have to play with.[/B][/QUOTE]

