 get a resist head piece, but I like my custom Velious helm more (or my Crown of the Froglok Kings).<P>------------------<BR>-<A HREF="http://www.guildsay.com/guilds/view_character.php?id=1" TARGET=_blank>Heffling</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Escapee</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This one's easy  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Take the Lodizal Shield and put it on your back instead of the heiro cloak.  Then use a sarnak battle shield (AC:25/Str:5/Sta:5/HP:40/FR:10/CR:10/MR:10) for your shield slot.  You end up losing the +75 mana, but you gain 15ac and a bunch of resists for it.  That removes 4 wis.<P>Replace the coldain skin gloves with Crystal Chitin Gauntlets (AC:20/Str:10/Mana:35).  This is a good option if like AC though I can see how some like the hp/sta of the coldain skin gloves.  That removes 6 wis.<P>Replace the obulous death shroud with Imbued Granite Spaulders (AC:20/MR:10/CR:10/FR:10/PR:10/DR:10), if your race allows it.  If you are low on str, the gloves above help a lot with that.  That removes 3 wis.<P>You can do what I did and replace the EM Greaves with Gladiator Chain Legs Gladiator's Chain Leggings (AC:17/Str:2/Wis:6/Chr:4/MR:10/HP:20) though I understand why some would think that EM are better (they certainly look better).  If you have high wis though, 17ac, 2str, 10mr, 20hp 0 weight is better than 15ac, 5str, 5agi, 7pr, weight 5.6 IMO.  This removes 3 wis.<P>The Supple Scale Armband for clerics isn't that good because of the low AC.  If you want to retain high AC and keep wis there is Coldain Military Wristguard (AC:10/Str:5/Wis:6/CR:5/MR:5).  If you want even more AC and don't care about wis there is of course Donal's Bracer of Mourning (AC:16/Effect:Pacify).  Since you listed the Forbitten Rites Arms, I assume you will eventually get the bracers as well Bracers of Forbidden Rites (AC:15/Wis:2/Agi:5/HP:35/FR:2/Effect:AbundantFood).  These choices range from adding one to wis to removing 5 from wis.<P>For the enshrouded veil, there is            Crystal Spider Eye's (AC:8/Mana:35/HP:35/Wgt:0).  You lose the 10fr (but you make that back by using the sarnak battle shield anyways  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> but can keep the veil for situational use.  This removes 2 wis.<P>Just some suggestions...<P>Escapee | E'ci</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Doctor1</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lodizal shield on back and get a OoIV for Off hand. You will actualy go up 1 in wis, but even better Add lots of AC.<P>My gear<BR>Fungi Tunic<BR>IGS<BR>RBG<BR>OoIV<BR>Lod Shield<BR>6ac 65hp (x2)<BR>MoW (9ac 9wis)<P>Gives me 205 wis, Very Nice AC Hp Mana adds and a 15pt Regen. <P>Doctor1</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Nemean:<BR><B>/jealous<P>High Elf at lv55 with only 188 WIS   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><BR>Really gotta get me a good BP or Legs - anyone know where in Kael these babies drop?  We been pharming the hell out of the arena area, and haven't seen one drop.<P>Nem.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Something 1000 times easier to get and will definitely put you over 200 wis is an Emerald Dragonscale BP. All you pretty much gotta do is kill Wuoshi and the rest is easy. Yields a +20 wis BP that'll tide you over til you can get a ToV one.<P>As to the dropping wis part...<P>Get some Velious gauntlets, Jubal. None of them have +wis but they all have +mana and are rich in AC and have a few other stats.<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>Erudite Templar of Prexus<BR><A HREF="http://www.cohort.cc" TARGET=_blank>Cohort Chalybeius</A><BR>Cazic Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Siren</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I didn't put all my starting points into wis and actually have a base wis of 98, and am still sitting at 230ish wis now.  It's unavoidable!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ladas Sindarin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I don't completely understand the dissatisfaction with high end gear with lots of wisdom when it also has other needed stats, regardless of your current wisdom level.<P>Well, let me qualify that.  I do realize that there is a point of diminishing returns from wisdom post 200 compared to other stats, such as AC, HP, Mana and resists.<P>However, I see enough comments, many like the ones in this thread, lamenting the levels of their wisdom over 200 and commenting that they wish Verant would quit putting wisdom on top tier items.  Why?<P>Those same top tier items also tend to have high AC/HP/Sta/Resists, so all your bases are covered.  And even if each point of wisdom over 200 is only worth 1 mana, for those with 240+ wisdom, thats an extra 40 Mana.. and I see casters drool over items that add similiar amounts of raw mana.<P>Seems to me the title of this thread just translates to "Can't get rid of extra mana", and I was of the impression more mana is always good.  But then I play a ranger who just muddles through your boards, so please enlighten me.<p>[This message has been edited by Ladas Sindarin (edited 08-09-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Haxx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mostly because, it seems like it's going to waste. If they put more hp/mana/resists on the item instead of putting pointless wisdom, I would be infinitely happier  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>With full resist gear on, I still have 222wis (180+ to all resists). This is, like I said, with 90 base.<P>My point, was that I wish Verant would realize that we don't *need*/*want* more wisdom and would rather have higher hp/mana/resists on our items instead.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Splaktar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Jubal:<BR><B><BR>First, the uber stuff that I assume I will be wearing for a very long time:<P>Lodizal Shell Shield (10 wis) - put this on your back, wear sarnak or kunark dragon shield or draco's shield<P>Girdle of Grotesque (10 wis)<P>The next level of items are things that have good stats for mana, hp, sta etc.:<P>Heirophant's Cloak (4 wis) - sell this<BR>Coldain skin gloves (6 wis) - sell this, get Donals or Crazy Cleric or even Gaunlets of the Black<BR>Ethereal mist BP (15 wis)<BR>Ethereal mist legs (9 wis) - replace with Crazy Cleric Legs, this will drop you 9 wis, also Guardian legs for raids 15fr/15cr/5mr will drop you 4 wis<BR>Obolus death shroud (3 wis) - Destroy this, get a WotG<BR>Vambraces of Forbidden Rites (3 wis)<P>Finally I have the things that give WIS but I really dont have anything better to replace them with:<P>Dawnfire (7 wis)<BR>Supple Scale armband (5 wis) - any velious bracer has way more than 5ac, plus can summon you food   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><BR>Enshrouded Veil (2 wis)<BR></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>------------------<BR>Splaktar/Gurgel/Samas<p>[This message has been edited by Splaktar (edited 08-10-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thistleburr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Greetings!<P>Since I basically raid all the time I wear resistance gear. My wisdom runs between 179 and 200 depending on the nature of the encounter.<P>I get no wisdom from the following slots:<P>Head, ears, face, neck, fingers, wrists, chest, secondary, range, feet.<P>Unbuffed resists are all above 100 with the specific unbuffed resists for a given fight at 200. Split resists (magic/fire, fire/cold, magic/disease) run around unbuffed 170's. Hit 452MR with a bard last night  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR><B>Thistleburr</B>, High Priestess of Bristlebane<BR><A HREF="http://www.the-elitists.com" TARGET=_blank><I>The Elitists</I></A>, Tribunal Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok... decided to sell the heiro cloak, and I put the lod shield on my back. I'm using a SBS as my shield now. Also managed to get rid of the supple scale bracer with a brand new Symbol of Tunarean Worship! (first on Torv)<P>I wish I had access to some of the other items you guys have mentioned (OoIV, Crazy Cleric gear) but unfortunately I dont... yet. Draco's gonna drop me a shield one of these days though  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>I have a full set of resist gear - a pair of BD bracers, diamond rings, BD earrings, gold diamond mask, and assorted odds and ends that boost resists here and there. I keep all this stuff in a pair of tinkerer's bags and haul it around with me cause I never know when I'll have to rush off to a raid somewhere.<P>I do have to say that it's very weird when you hit the turning point on WIS, where you hit 200+ without trying rather than agonizing over how much AC you're willing to sacrifice to get your WIS that high. WIS is now 213 without wearing a single piece of gear specifically for that stat.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Caleal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I love all the extra wis! <BR>My normal walk around gear has me at 237 wis, 1125 ac and all resists from 79-125. The way I see it, all the extra wis on the high end gear is 